On the subject of CoffeeScript and React/JSX, our team uses something like this[1] to reduce the need for `React.DOM[...]` or lots of `requires` to components.<p>Our components end up looking like this. As a CoffeeScript/Jade fan, I obviously like it:<p><pre><code>    ReactElementBuilder = require &#x27;./lib/react-element-builder&#x27;

    # Example: add react-bootstrap components.
    ReactElementBuilder.addMany require(&#x27;react-bootstrap&#x27;)

    MyComponent = React.createClass
      mixins: [ReactElementBuilder.mixin]

      render: ->
        @e &#x27;div#main&#x27;, null,

          @e &#x27;Navbar.fixed&#x27;,
            onClick: @handleNavbarClick
            &#x27;Hello my name is Navbar&#x27;
</code></pre>
[1]: <a href="https://gist.github.com/mikew/e737273e42ed704c6c54" rel="nofollow">https://gist.github.com/mikew/e737273e42ed704c6c54</a>

